WEBVTT

00:00.768 --> 00:03.137
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.413 --> 00:15.649
-* SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS *

00:16.517 --> 00:20.688
* AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT *

00:20.788 --> 00:22.390
* SOME PEOPLE NEED

00:22.490 --> 00:24.192
* TO HELP SOMEBODY

00:24.292 --> 00:27.761
* WHEN THE EDGE
OF SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT *

00:27.861 --> 00:30.331
* DON'T YOU WORRY

00:30.431 --> 00:33.734
* IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

00:36.537 --> 00:38.406
* 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.506 --> 00:42.243
* I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT *

00:45.213 --> 00:47.415
* I'LL BE THERE

00:47.515 --> 00:49.049
* I'LL BE READY

00:49.150 --> 00:51.252
* WHENEVER YOU FEAR

00:51.352 --> 00:53.053
* OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:53.154 --> 00:56.290
* I'LL BE READY

00:56.390 --> 00:59.427
* FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.527 --> 01:02.230
* I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.581 --> 01:22.383
* 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.483 --> 01:26.154
* I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT *

01:27.588 --> 01:28.489
* OH!

01:28.589 --> 01:31.459
* I'LL BE READY

01:31.559 --> 01:33.361
* I'LL BE READY

01:33.461 --> 01:35.163
* WHENEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.263 --> 01:37.198
* OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.298 --> 01:40.201
* I'LL BE READY

01:40.601 --> 01:43.437
* FOREVER AND ALWAYS *

01:43.537 --> 01:46.574
* I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:36.457 --> 02:37.558
-G'MORNING.

02:38.492 --> 02:39.960
-GOOD MORNING.

02:40.060 --> 02:42.496
-TAKING THE DAY OFF?
-NO, JUST TAKING THE MORNING OFF.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.699
COULD YOU MOVE YOUR TRUCK?
IT'S BLOCKING MY VIEW.

02:47.034 --> 02:48.369
-DON'T FORGET TO TURN OVER.

02:48.469 --> 02:50.304
I DON'T WANNA SEE YOU
GO HOME HALF BAKED.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.240
-TURN ME OVER
ON YOUR WAY BACK.

02:52.340 --> 02:53.807
-SURE.

02:55.142 --> 02:56.544
-BYE.

02:58.812 --> 03:01.215
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I JUST SAID THAT.

03:10.123 --> 03:12.960
-BOYS, BOYS!
YOU'RE GETTING SAND ALL OVER.

03:13.060 --> 03:14.428
WATCH THESE WILD INDIANS.

03:14.528 --> 03:15.729
-DON'T SPLASH.

03:15.829 --> 03:17.164
-NOW, I WANT YOU
TO EAT SOMETHING.

03:17.265 --> 03:19.600
-[CHATTERING]

03:56.203 --> 03:57.237
-HI.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.806
-[SILENT]

04:02.209 --> 04:03.811
-DON'T BE SHY.

04:03.911 --> 04:04.845
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

04:04.945 --> 04:08.482
-[LOUD MUSIC PLAYING]

04:12.052 --> 04:14.755
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

04:58.098 --> 04:59.299
-HEY.

05:01.369 --> 05:03.036
NOBODY COMPLAINED
ABOUT THAT MUSIC?

05:03.136 --> 05:05.005
-EVERYBODY IS COMPLAINING.

05:05.105 --> 05:07.608
I ASK THEM TO TURN IT DOWN,
FIVE MINUTES LATER
IT'S BLASTING AGAIN.

05:07.708 --> 05:10.310
MAYBE YOU CAN CHARM THEM
INTO PERMANENT SUBMISSION.

05:10.411 --> 05:12.513
-MAYBE YOU COULD
BE BACK IN 15 MINUTES?

05:12.613 --> 05:15.315
-YOU KNOW, WE OUGHTA JUST
COME UP WITH A NEW
LIFEGUARD COMPETITION.

05:15.416 --> 05:16.450
RUN, EAT, RUN.

05:17.117 --> 05:19.052
NEXT TIME, I'LL JUST
DO WHAT HARVEY DOES

05:19.152 --> 05:20.588
AND I'LL ORDER DOMINOES.

05:24.758 --> 05:26.159
-EXCUSE ME,
HAVE YOU SEEN A LITTLE GIRL?

05:26.259 --> 05:28.629
SHE'S ABOUT THAT SIZE.
SHE'S GOT A FRENCH BRAID.

05:29.129 --> 05:30.364
THANK YOU.

05:32.566 --> 05:34.968
EXCUSE ME, MISS, HAVE YOU
SEEN MY LITTLE GIRL?

05:35.068 --> 05:36.937
SHE'S WEARING
A FLOWERED BATHING SUIT.

05:37.037 --> 05:38.772
SHE HAS A LITTLE
FRENCH BRAID IN HER HAIR.

05:38.872 --> 05:41.542
-YES, I DID, AND SHE WENT
THAT WAY ABOUT FIVE MINUTES AGO.

05:41.642 --> 05:42.543
-THIS WAY?
-UH-HUH.

05:42.643 --> 05:43.944
-THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

05:44.044 --> 05:45.679
-EXCUSE ME, MISS,
IF YOU CAN'T FIND HER,

05:45.779 --> 05:46.980
YOU SHOULD TELL
THE LIFEGUARDS.

05:47.080 --> 05:48.416
THEY FIND LOST CHILDREN
ALL THE TIME.

05:48.516 --> 05:50.150
WHAT'S HER NAME?
-IT'S LILI,

05:50.250 --> 05:52.352
BUT IT DOESN'T MATTER.
SHE WON'T HEAR IT.
SHE'S DEAF.

05:55.088 --> 05:59.460
-[MUSIC CONTINUES]

06:10.037 --> 06:11.071
-HELLO, LADIES.

06:11.171 --> 06:12.239
ENJOYING YOURSELVES?

06:12.740 --> 06:14.274
DO YOU SEE
THIS DOLPHIN OVER HERE?

06:14.374 --> 06:15.576
GREAT, HUH?

06:16.276 --> 06:18.211
EXCUSE ME, COULD I
TALK TO YOU FOR A SECOND?

06:18.311 --> 06:19.212
-SURE.

06:20.347 --> 06:23.183
-COULD YOU DO ME
A REAL BIG FAVOR?
-WHAT?

06:23.283 --> 06:26.153
-WELL, YOU SEE, I NEED TO HEAR
IF SOMEONE NEEDS HELP.

06:26.654 --> 06:29.423
COULD YOU TURN THE STEREO DOWN
JUST A LITTLE BIT?

06:29.523 --> 06:31.024
-OKAY, HOW FAR?

06:31.559 --> 06:32.926
-ALMOST ALL THE WAY.

06:33.026 --> 06:35.496
-[LAUGHING]

06:36.597 --> 06:37.898
-MAN ON RADIO:
ATTENTION SURFERS.

06:37.998 --> 06:40.267
BATTEN THE HATCHES.
THIS JUST IN.

06:40.367 --> 06:41.935
A SWELL OF EPIC PROPORTIONS

06:42.035 --> 06:43.837
SPAWNED BY
A MASSIVE TYPHOON

06:43.937 --> 06:46.039
IN THE SOUTH SEAS
IS HEADED OUR WAY.

06:46.139 --> 06:48.408
WAVES EXPECTED TO REACH
ENORMOUS HEIGHTS

06:48.509 --> 06:52.846
THAT COULD MATCH
THE FABLED BIG MONDAY SWELL
OF SOME 30 YEARS BACK.

06:53.313 --> 06:54.582
STAY TUNED, SURFERS.

06:54.682 --> 06:58.185
MORE INFO ON BIG MONDAY,
THE SEQUEL, LATER.

06:58.285 --> 06:59.687
YOW!

07:27.047 --> 07:28.315
-LIFEGUARD!

07:28.415 --> 07:31.151
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

07:34.421 --> 07:37.024
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

07:37.558 --> 07:39.760
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

07:47.000 --> 07:49.603
-SHE'S DEAF.
SHE WON'T BE ABLE TO HEAR YOU.

07:52.439 --> 07:54.542
-[CRYING]

08:53.867 --> 08:55.202
IS SHE ALIVE?

08:56.570 --> 08:57.537
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

08:57.638 --> 08:59.640
-OKAY.
-LILI.

09:00.207 --> 09:01.408
-OKAY. PLEASE.

09:01.809 --> 09:03.543
-PLEASE.
IS SHE BREATHING?

09:04.177 --> 09:05.378
LILI, BREATHE.

09:05.478 --> 09:07.114
BREATHE FOR MOMMY.

09:14.855 --> 09:16.189
-LET ME THROUGH.

09:22.362 --> 09:23.664
-COMING THROUGH.

09:30.804 --> 09:33.406
-[CRYING]
MY BABY.

09:33.506 --> 09:35.542
WHY WON'T SHE BREATHE?

09:35.643 --> 09:36.944
-COME ON, BABY.

09:37.044 --> 09:38.612
COME ON.

09:43.851 --> 09:45.385
-[COUGHS]
-YEAH, ATTA GIRL.

09:45.485 --> 09:46.419
ATTA GIRL.

09:46.519 --> 09:48.155
YEAH, OKAY.

09:48.789 --> 09:50.023
OKAY.

09:53.661 --> 09:57.297
-[CRYING]
THAT'S MY GIRL.

09:57.397 --> 09:58.666
OH, LILI.

10:03.637 --> 10:05.005
-MITCH, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:05.605 --> 10:06.940
-YEAH, I'M FINE.

10:07.040 --> 10:08.275
-HOW LONG WAS SHE IN THERE?

10:08.375 --> 10:11.078
-I DON'T KNOW.
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:11.679 --> 10:13.446
-SOMEONE ELSE
GOT TO HER FIRST.

10:13.546 --> 10:14.715
-WHO?

10:17.384 --> 10:20.053
-I'M SO SORRY.
SHE MUST HAVE WANDERED OFF.

10:20.153 --> 10:21.188
-OH, IT'S OKAY.

10:23.323 --> 10:24.291
WHAT IS IT, HONEY?

10:29.663 --> 10:32.365
-THIS YOURS?
-NO, NO, IT'S NOT HERS.

10:35.535 --> 10:36.737
-THANK YOU.

10:57.024 --> 10:59.126
-WORLD FAMOUS CHICKEN
OF THE SEA.

10:59.226 --> 11:01.594
WHAT'S THE MATTER, CHICKEN?
WAVES TOO BIG?

11:01.695 --> 11:03.697
-YEAH, THEY ARE.
NOT.

11:03.797 --> 11:05.632
-THEN WHY ARE YOU
SO FAR BEHIND THE BREAK?

11:05.733 --> 11:07.901
-I'M JUST WAITING
FOR A GOOD SET.

11:08.001 --> 11:09.602
-WHAT?
THE ONE-FOOTERS?

11:09.703 --> 11:12.339
[LAUGHS]

11:13.140 --> 11:15.575
DON'T WORRY, CHICKEN.
YOU'RE DADDY'S A LIFEGUARD.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.077
HE'LL SAVE YOU.

11:17.177 --> 11:19.947
[CLUCKING]

11:55.749 --> 11:58.285
-HEY.
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?

12:02.389 --> 12:03.556
-I BLEW THAT RESCUE.

12:04.657 --> 12:07.660
-MITCH, A CIVILIAN HAPPENED
TO BE CLOSER TO THE VICTIM
THAN YOU.

12:07.761 --> 12:08.862
THAT'S ALL.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.532
-SHAUNI, IF SOMEONE
HADN'T YELLED, I WOULDN'T
HAVE EVEN SEEN HER.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.402
IF THAT HAWAIIAN GUY
WASN'T IN THE WATER...

12:16.569 --> 12:18.038
SHE MIGHT HAVE DROWNED.

12:20.040 --> 12:22.575
-DO YOU KNOW WHO THAT GUY WAS
OR WHERE HE CAME FROM?

12:22.675 --> 12:23.710
-NO.

12:23.811 --> 12:26.346
HE JUST SURFACED

12:27.080 --> 12:28.515
AND HE WAS HOLDING HER.

12:31.618 --> 12:33.286
LOOKED LIKE KANALOA.

12:34.421 --> 12:35.488
-LIKE WHO?

12:35.588 --> 12:38.826
-YOU KNOW KANALOA?
IT'S A HAWAIIAN GOD.

12:41.194 --> 12:42.762
-DO YOU THINK
THAT WAS HIS?

12:45.265 --> 12:46.900
THE GUY'S.
NOT THE GOD'S.

12:48.768 --> 12:51.038
-THE LITTLE GIRLS MUST HAVE
PULLED IT FROM AROUND HIS NECK.

12:52.840 --> 12:54.307
-SO WHAT HAPPENED,
MITCH?

12:56.243 --> 12:58.045
WHY'D YOU MISS
THAT RESCUE?

12:59.146 --> 13:00.881
-YOU EVER HEAR
OF BIG MONDAY?

13:01.648 --> 13:03.216
-YEAH, I READ ABOUT IT.

13:03.316 --> 13:06.786
IT'S KIND OF HARD TO IMAGINE
30-FOOT WAVES ON THIS BEACH.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.289
-SHAUNI, IT WAS 1961.

13:10.057 --> 13:11.291
I WAS SEVEN YEARS OLD.

13:11.791 --> 13:12.960
IT WAS RIGHT HERE.

13:14.127 --> 13:17.831
I CAN REMEMBER
THESE HUGE WAVES.

13:18.731 --> 13:20.067
BUT THAT'S ALL
I CAN REMEMBER.

13:21.434 --> 13:22.903
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,
TODAY,

13:23.370 --> 13:25.272
WHEN I HEARD
ON THE RADIO

13:25.372 --> 13:27.975
FROM THAT DISC JOCKEY
THAT ANOTHER BIG MONDAY
WAS COMING...

13:28.876 --> 13:30.911
I DON'T KNOW.
IT TRIGGERED SOMETHING.

13:32.245 --> 13:34.447
SUDDENLY,
I WAS SEVEN YEARS OLD AGAIN...

13:36.183 --> 13:38.018
STANDING ON THAT BEACH...

13:39.219 --> 13:41.821
WATCHING THIS HUGE WAVE...

13:42.589 --> 13:44.491
ABOUT TO COME OVER ME.

13:45.492 --> 13:47.460
-SO DO YOU THINK
THAT'S WHAT DISTRACTED YOU?

13:48.095 --> 13:49.196
-I DON'T KNOW.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.000
I DO KNOW ONE THING...

13:54.467 --> 13:57.204
THE THOUGHT OF ANOTHER
BIG MONDAY SCARES
THE HELL OUT OF ME.

14:16.389 --> 14:17.490
-HANK!

14:17.590 --> 14:19.459
THE LIFEGUARDS SAY SHE'S
GONNA BE JUST FINE.

14:20.027 --> 14:21.461
BECAUSE THEY HAD
TO CHECK HER OUT.

14:21.561 --> 14:22.595
YES.

14:23.130 --> 14:25.198
YES, WE'LL WAIT RIGHT HERE
FOR YOU, SWEETHEART.

14:25.298 --> 14:26.366
BYE.

14:30.270 --> 14:32.439
-YOUR NAME IS LILI.

14:32.539 --> 14:35.208
L-I-L-I.

14:36.609 --> 14:39.312
-MY HUSBAND TOOK
OUR OTHER KIDS
TO HIS MOTHER'S.

14:39.412 --> 14:41.448
HE'LL BE BACK TO PICK US UP
IN ABOUT AN HOUR OR SO.

14:41.548 --> 14:44.551
-OH GOOD, THAT WILL GIVE ME
MORE TIME TO TEACH LILI
HER NAME.

14:44.651 --> 14:46.286
I'M SHOWING HER
HOW TO SIGN HER NAME.

14:46.386 --> 14:49.189
L-I-L-I.

14:49.289 --> 14:50.857
THAT'S YOUR NAME.

14:50.958 --> 14:53.326
-LIKE I TOLD YOU,
LILI DOESN'T UNDERSTAND
SIGN LANGUAGE.

14:53.426 --> 14:55.295
-IF YOU WOULD LIKE HER
TO LEARN,

14:55.395 --> 14:57.164
I HAVE SOME FRIENDS
THAT RUN A SCHOOL,

14:57.264 --> 14:59.166
AND THEY CAN TEACH
YOUR WHOLE FAMILY TO SIGN.

14:59.266 --> 15:02.235
-NO, THANK YOU.
WE DON'T BELIEVE IN THAT.

15:02.335 --> 15:03.870
WE WANT LILI
TO GROW UP NORMAL.

15:03.971 --> 15:05.772
NOT HAVE OTHER PEOPLE TREAT HER
AS THOUGH SHE'S DIFFERENT.

15:05.872 --> 15:07.174
-MRS. SEGER,

15:07.274 --> 15:09.042
LILI IS DIFFERENT.

15:09.142 --> 15:10.910
AND THAT'S NOT BAD.

15:11.378 --> 15:14.314
BUT SHE'S DEAF, AND SHE NEEDS
A WAY TO EXPRESS TO YOU

15:14.414 --> 15:16.383
WHAT SHE THINKS,
AND HOW SHE FEELS,

15:16.483 --> 15:18.085
AND THE THINGS
THAT SHE WANTS.

15:18.551 --> 15:21.921
LEARNING SIGN LANGUAGE
CAN JUST OPEN UP
A WHOLE NEW WORLD FOR HER.

15:22.022 --> 15:25.092
-BUT SHE'S ALREADY LEARNING
A LANGUAGE, JUST LIKE
EVERYONE ELSE.

15:25.925 --> 15:27.727
LILI, SAY THANK YOU.

15:27.827 --> 15:29.762
[SILENT]

15:30.263 --> 15:31.664
-[INDISTINCT]

15:31.764 --> 15:33.166
-GOOD GIRL.

15:35.002 --> 15:36.303
YOU SEE?

15:36.403 --> 15:38.571
MRS. SEGER, LIP READING
AND BEING ABLE TO SPEAK,

15:38.671 --> 15:41.641
THAT'S ALL WONDERFUL,
BUT THAT'S REALLY
LIMITED FOR HER.

15:41.741 --> 15:44.811
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME
DRIVE YOU DOWN TO THE SCHOOL
SO YOU CAN SEE--

15:44.911 --> 15:46.213
-MOM!
-WHAT, HONEY?

15:46.313 --> 15:47.780
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

15:47.880 --> 15:49.983
WHAT?
-[GROANS]

15:55.588 --> 15:56.856
-WHAT IS IT?

15:56.956 --> 15:58.725
-[INDISTINCT]
-HONEY, WHAT?

15:58.825 --> 16:00.427
-MOMMY!
-LILI, DON'T.

16:00.527 --> 16:01.828
DON'T, LILI.

16:01.928 --> 16:03.796
LILI, SWEETHEART.
-[SHOUTS]

16:03.896 --> 16:05.132
-MRS. SEGER.

16:05.232 --> 16:07.267
-[SHOUTING]
-LILI, LILI, LILI, NO.

16:07.367 --> 16:09.669
LILI, LOOK AT MOMMY.
WHAT'S WRONG?

16:09.769 --> 16:11.071
-MRS. SEGER.

16:11.171 --> 16:13.940
PLEASE, I THINK I KNOW
WHAT SHE WANTS.

16:14.041 --> 16:16.143
COULD I TAKE HER, PLEASE?

16:23.483 --> 16:25.985
OKAY.
DO YOU WANT

16:26.086 --> 16:27.687
TO SEE THE FISH?

16:27.787 --> 16:28.755
YEAH?
-[GROANS]

16:30.157 --> 16:33.660
-OH, YOU WANT
TO FEED THE FISH.

16:37.197 --> 16:38.765
WE'LL FEED THE FISH.

16:38.865 --> 16:39.999
OKAY.

16:41.601 --> 16:42.735
HERE WE GO.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.538
WE GOT SOME FOOD RIGHT HERE.

16:46.139 --> 16:47.774
HERE YOU-- I'LL OPEN IT.
OKAY.

16:49.409 --> 16:51.544
YOU KNOW, MRS. SEGER,
IF SHE KNEW SIGN LANGUAGE

16:51.644 --> 16:55.248
SHE WOULD HAVE BEEN ABLE
TO TELL US EXACTLY WHAT
SHE WANTED TO DO.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.784
SHE WOULD HAVE SAID
I WANT TO

16:58.218 --> 16:59.552
FEED THE FISH.

17:04.391 --> 17:06.393
I KNOW YOU LOVE
LILI A LOT.

17:07.094 --> 17:10.663
PLEASE GIVE HER THE CHANCE
TO TELL YOU HOW SHE FEELS
ABOUT BEING DEAF.

17:21.340 --> 17:22.608
-SEE YOU TOMORROW, HOB!

17:23.710 --> 17:24.676
HOBIE!

17:40.227 --> 17:42.195
HEY, HOB,
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

17:42.962 --> 17:43.930
-NOTHING.

17:44.764 --> 17:46.333
-COME ON, YOU CAN
TALK TO ME.

17:46.433 --> 17:47.634
SIT DOWN.
COME ON.

17:50.137 --> 17:51.438
WHAT'S GOING ON?

17:53.306 --> 17:54.541
-I'M A CHICKEN.

17:54.641 --> 17:55.608
-SAYS WHO?

17:56.276 --> 17:57.777
-CLAY.

17:58.711 --> 17:59.646
BILLY.

18:00.713 --> 18:01.748
EVERYONE.

18:03.216 --> 18:04.151
THEY'RE RIGHT,
I AM.

18:04.251 --> 18:05.685
-SINCE WHEN?

18:07.019 --> 18:08.388
-LAST WEEK.

18:09.222 --> 18:11.624
I DROPPED INTO THIS WAVE.
IT WAS HOLLOW.

18:12.759 --> 18:14.861
I WAS UNDER
FOR A REALLY LONG TIME.

18:17.497 --> 18:19.366
I JUST REALLY SKETCHED.

18:20.367 --> 18:23.136
AND EVER SINCE I'VE BEEN
CHICKEN TO RIDE ON A WAVE.

18:24.036 --> 18:24.937
-LISTEN, HOBIE.

18:25.505 --> 18:27.674
EVERYBODY GETS
SCARED SOMETIMES,

18:27.774 --> 18:31.010
AND ANYBODY WHO TELLS YOU
ANYTHING DIFFERENT IS A LIAR.

18:31.911 --> 18:34.113
YOU ARE GONNA BE BACK
OUT THERE IN NO TIME AT ALL.

18:34.214 --> 18:36.449
-YOU REALLY THINK SO?
-DEFINITELY.

18:39.652 --> 18:40.653
-UM, SHAUNI?

18:41.221 --> 18:43.390
-WHAT?
-MY DAD'S GOING OUT TONIGHT.

18:43.490 --> 18:45.892
YOU WANT TO COME OVER
AND WATCH SOME SURFING VIDEOS?

18:45.992 --> 18:47.727
-YEAH, I'D LIKE THAT.

18:47.827 --> 18:50.330
EDDIE'S NOT BACK YET
FROM THE LIFEGUARD COMPETITION

18:50.430 --> 18:51.798
SO I AM A FREE WOMAN.

18:52.199 --> 18:53.166
IT'LL BE GREAT.

18:53.266 --> 18:54.734
-DON'T TELL MY DAD.

18:55.902 --> 18:58.137
I MEAN, ABOUT ME
BEING SCARED AND ALL.

18:58.238 --> 18:59.306
-OKAY,

18:59.772 --> 19:02.041
BUT, HOBIE, I REALLY THINK
THAT YOU SHOULD.

19:02.509 --> 19:04.977
I KNOW YOUR DAD.
I KNOW HE'D UNDERSTAND.

19:05.077 --> 19:06.479
-NO, HE WON'T.

19:07.480 --> 19:09.682
HE'S NEVER BEEN
SCARED OF ANYTHING.

19:10.483 --> 19:12.352
DON'T TELL HIM.
PLEASE?

19:12.452 --> 19:13.686
-ALL RIGHT.

19:14.554 --> 19:16.456
BUT YOU REMEMBER
WHAT I SAID, HOBIE.

19:16.556 --> 19:18.925
EVERYBODY GETS
SCARED SOMETIMES.

19:19.759 --> 19:20.827
EVEN YOUR DAD.

19:38.311 --> 19:39.412
-DISC JOCKEY:
YO, SURFERS.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.013
THE COUNTDOWN HAS BEGUN.

19:41.113 --> 19:44.517
THE WEATHER FAIRY PREDICTS
THAT BIG MONDAY THE SEQUEL

19:44.617 --> 19:46.853
WILL PREMIER ON,
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT,

19:46.953 --> 19:48.054
MONDAY MORNING.

19:48.154 --> 19:49.456
SAME DAY AS BEFORE.

19:49.556 --> 19:50.990
WHAT A MIND BLOWER.

19:51.090 --> 19:53.226
DEJA VU ALL OVER AGAIN.

19:53.326 --> 19:55.495
YOW! SURFS UP.

20:08.775 --> 20:10.443
-[CARS HONKING]

