32:09.561 --> 32:10.329
YOU KNOW?

32:11.363 --> 32:14.933
WHAT DO YOU DO WHEN YOU
GET SCARED OF SOMETHING
YOU'VE ALWAYS LOVED TO DO?

32:16.969 --> 32:18.304
-COME HERE.

32:21.807 --> 32:23.042
WELL.

32:25.311 --> 32:28.080
I THINK YOU JUST GET
BACK OUT THERE
AND DO IT AGAIN.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.497
THIS HELPED ME
FIND MY WAVE.

32:46.098 --> 32:47.899
-AS I SAID.

32:48.500 --> 32:51.637
THERE'S ALWAYS ONE
YOU NEVER FORGET

32:51.737 --> 32:54.006
AS LONG AS YOU LIVE.

32:56.275 --> 32:58.044
-BUT I DID FORGET THIS ONE.

33:00.679 --> 33:02.148
LAST NIGHT I REMEMBERED.

33:07.319 --> 33:08.754
I WAS SEVEN YEARS OLD,

33:09.455 --> 33:11.123
STANDING ON THE BEACH.

33:12.391 --> 33:14.426
THIS WAVE WAS BREAKING
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

33:15.527 --> 33:16.662
IT WAS HUGE.

33:17.896 --> 33:19.565
SO I TURNED AND RAN.

33:21.567 --> 33:24.270
ANOTHER BOY STANDING
RIGHT NEXT TO ME DIDN'T.

33:26.138 --> 33:27.373
WHEN I TURNED BACK,

33:28.040 --> 33:29.775
I SAW THE WAVE
BREAKING OVER...

33:30.809 --> 33:32.244
RIGHT ON TOP OF HIM.

33:35.914 --> 33:37.716
I JUST FROZE.

33:41.087 --> 33:42.454
HE DROWNED.

33:43.889 --> 33:45.424
-YOU WERE A BOY.

33:45.924 --> 33:47.793
NOW, YOU'RE A MAN.

33:47.893 --> 33:50.996
YOU DIDN'T KNOW HOW
TO SAVE NO ONE THEN.

33:51.097 --> 33:52.931
-I COULD HAVE TRIED,
CLARENCE.

33:53.565 --> 33:56.435
-HOW MANY PEOPLE,
HOW MANY LIVES

33:56.535 --> 33:58.036
YOU SAVE SINCE THEN, HUH?

33:59.671 --> 34:01.273
-I DON'T KNOW.

34:02.774 --> 34:04.843
MAYBE A HUNDRED.
-A HUNDRED PEOPLE,

34:04.943 --> 34:08.080
WHO LIVE NOW BECAUSE OF YOU,
NEVER DIED THEN?

34:11.417 --> 34:13.319
A HUNDRED PEOPLE.

34:16.755 --> 34:18.224
AND HOBIE.

35:00.499 --> 35:02.968
